---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ConceptNav from '../../components/ConceptNav.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Scenario-Driven + Test-First — OpenLogos" description="One scenario ID traces from requirements to verified code. Tests define 'done' before a line is written.">
  <ConceptNav current="scenario-test-first" />
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="hero-tag tag-green">Core Principle</div>
      <h1>Scenario-Driven.<br/><span class="gradient-text">Test-First.</span></h1>
      <p class="hero-desc">One scenario ID traces from the first requirement to the last line of verified code. Tests define "done" before a single line is written. Quality becomes a number — not a feeling. This is Harness Engineering's <em>evaluation &amp; observation layer</em> — made measurable.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Scenario Journey -->
  <section class="journey-section">
    <div class="container-wide">
      <div class="section-label">The Scenario Journey</div>
      <h2 class="section-title">One ID. Three phases. Complete traceability.</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">Follow scenario <code>S01</code> from a one-sentence pain point to automated acceptance.</p>

      <div class="journey">
        <div class="journey-phase">
          <div class="journey-header phase-why">
            <span class="phase-label">Phase 1 · WHY</span>
            <span class="phase-id">S01</span>
          </div>
          <div class="journey-body">
            <div class="journey-quote">"Users need to register with email"</div>
            <div class="journey-artifacts">
              <div class="artifact"><span class="a-label">Pain Point</span> P01: No way to create an account</div>
              <div class="artifact"><span class="a-label">Acceptance</span> GIVEN valid email WHEN submit THEN account created</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="journey-connector">
          <div class="connector-line"></div>
          <div class="connector-label">Same S01</div>
        </div>

        <div class="journey-phase">
          <div class="journey-header phase-what">
            <span class="phase-label">Phase 2 · WHAT</span>
            <span class="phase-id">S01</span>
          </div>
          <div class="journey-body">
            <div class="journey-artifacts">
              <div class="artifact"><span class="a-label">Pages</span> Registration form → Success page</div>
              <div class="artifact"><span class="a-label">Fields</span> email (required, format), password (min 8)</div>
              <div class="artifact"><span class="a-label">States</span> loading, success, error (duplicate email)</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="journey-connector">
          <div class="connector-line"></div>
          <div class="connector-label">Same S01</div>
        </div>

        <div class="journey-phase">
          <div class="journey-header phase-how">
            <span class="phase-label">Phase 3 · HOW</span>
            <span class="phase-id">S01</span>
          </div>
          <div class="journey-body">
            <div class="journey-artifacts">
              <div class="artifact"><span class="a-label">Step 1</span> Sequence diagram → POST /auth/register</div>
              <div class="artifact"><span class="a-label">Step 2</span> OpenAPI YAML + users table DDL</div>
              <div class="artifact"><span class="a-label">Step 3</span> 12 test cases: UT-S01-001 … ST-S01-012</div>
              <div class="artifact"><span class="a-label">Step 4</span> AI generates code + test code</div>
              <div class="artifact artifact-pass"><span class="a-label">Step 5</span> openlogos verify → Gate 3.5 PASS ✓</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="journey-insight">
        <strong>No traceability matrix needed.</strong> The scenario ID <em>is</em> the trace. Change a requirement for S01? You know exactly which API, tests, and code are affected.
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Test-First -->
  <section class="testfirst-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-label">Test-First Methodology</div>
      <h2 class="section-title">Define "done" before writing code</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">This is not traditional TDD. It's designing the <em>entire test system</em> before any implementation.</p>

      <div class="compare">
        <div class="compare-col compare-old">
          <div class="compare-header">Traditional TDD</div>
          <div class="compare-body">
            <div class="compare-step">Write one test</div>
            <div class="compare-arrow">↓</div>
            <div class="compare-step">Write code to pass it</div>
            <div class="compare-arrow">↓</div>
            <div class="compare-step">Refactor</div>
            <div class="compare-arrow">↓</div>
            <div class="compare-step dim">Repeat (code-level thinking)</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="compare-vs">vs</div>

        <div class="compare-col compare-new">
          <div class="compare-header">OpenLogos Test-First</div>
          <div class="compare-body">
            <div class="compare-step highlight">Design all test cases first</div>
            <div class="compare-arrow">↓</div>
            <div class="compare-step">Unit tests (function correctness)</div>
            <div class="compare-step">Scenario tests (cross-module flow)</div>
            <div class="compare-step">API orchestration tests (end-to-end)</div>
            <div class="compare-arrow">↓</div>
            <div class="compare-step highlight">Then AI generates code with full context</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="why-box">
        <h3>Why does this matter for AI?</h3>
        <p>When you tell AI "write a registration feature," it guesses what "done" means. When you tell AI "write code that passes these 12 test cases with IDs UT-S01-001 through ST-S01-012," it has a <strong>precise, verifiable target</strong>. The output quality difference is dramatic.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Verification Loop -->
  <section class="verify-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-label">Automated Verification</div>
      <h2 class="section-title">Quality is a number, not a feeling</h2>

      <div class="verify-pipeline">
        <div class="verify-step">
          <div class="v-num">1</div>
          <div class="v-body">
            <h4>Tests run</h4>
            <p><code>npm test</code> / <code>pytest</code> — any framework, any language</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="verify-step">
          <div class="v-num">2</div>
          <div class="v-body">
            <h4>Results captured</h4>
            <p>OpenLogos reporter writes each result to <code>test-results.jsonl</code></p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="verify-step">
          <div class="v-num">3</div>
          <div class="v-body">
            <h4>Three-layer verification</h4>
            <p><code>openlogos verify</code> checks coverage, pass rate, and AC traceability</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="verify-result">
        <div class="result-header">
          <span class="result-badge result-pass">PASS</span>
          Gate 3.5 — Acceptance Report
        </div>
        <div class="result-body">
          <div class="result-row"><span>Test pass rate</span><span class="result-value">76/76 (100%)</span></div>
          <div class="result-row"><span>Design-time coverage</span><span class="result-value">25/25 assertions ✓</span></div>
          <div class="result-row"><span>Acceptance criteria</span><span class="result-value">21/21 AC traced ✓</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="result-footer">From the OpenLogos CLI project — we eat our own dog food.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cta-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>See the full picture</h2>
      <p>Learn how Documents as Context completes the methodology.</p>
      <div class="cta-actions">
        <a href="/getting-started/quick-start" class="btn btn-primary">Quick Start</a>
        <a href="/deep-dive/documents-as-context" class="btn btn-ghost">Next: Documents as Context →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .container { max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 1.5rem; }
  .container-wide { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 1.5rem; }

  .page-hero { padding: 5rem 1.5rem 3rem; text-align: center; }
  .hero-tag { display: inline-block; padding: 0.25rem 0.75rem; border-radius: 100px; font-size: 0.7rem; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.06em; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .tag-green { background: rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.12); color: #10b981; border: 1px solid rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.25); }
  .page-hero h1 { font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem); font-weight: 900; letter-spacing: -0.04em; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .gradient-text { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #10b981, #3b82f6); -webkit-background-clip: text; -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent; background-clip: text; }
  .hero-desc { color: var(--color-text-muted); font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.7; max-width: 580px; margin: 0 auto; }

  .section-label { font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--color-primary); margin-bottom: 0.75rem; text-align: center; }
  .section-title { font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3.5vw, 2rem); font-weight: 800; letter-spacing: -0.03em; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; text-align: center; }
  .section-desc { color: var(--color-text-muted); font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.7; text-align: center; max-width: 560px; margin: 0 auto 3rem; }
  .section-desc code, .hero-desc code { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.88em; background: var(--color-surface); padding: 0.15rem 0.4rem; border-radius: 4px; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); }

  /* Journey */
  .journey-section { padding: 2rem 0 4rem; }

  .journey { display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; }

  .journey-phase { width: 100%; background: var(--color-surface); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: 14px; overflow: hidden; }
  .journey-header { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .phase-label { font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; }
  .phase-id { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.8rem; font-weight: 700; padding: 0.15rem 0.5rem; background: var(--color-surface-raised); border-radius: 4px; }
  .phase-why { background: rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.06); }
  .phase-why .phase-label { color: #f59e0b; }
  .phase-what { background: rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.06); }
  .phase-what .phase-label { color: #3b82f6; }
  .phase-how { background: rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.06); }
  .phase-how .phase-label { color: #10b981; }

  .journey-body { padding: 1.5rem; }
  .journey-quote { font-size: 1rem; font-style: italic; color: var(--color-text-secondary); margin-bottom: 1rem; padding-left: 1rem; border-left: 3px solid var(--color-border); }
  .journey-artifacts { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.5rem; }
  .artifact { font-size: 0.88rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary); display: flex; gap: 0.75rem; align-items: baseline; }
  .a-label { flex-shrink: 0; font-size: 0.7rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.04em; color: var(--color-text-muted); min-width: 80px; }
  .artifact-pass { color: #10b981; font-weight: 600; }

  .journey-connector { display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; gap: 0; padding: 0.25rem 0; }
  .connector-line { width: 2px; height: 24px; background: var(--color-border); }
  .connector-label { font-size: 0.65rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-text-muted); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; padding: 0.2rem 0.5rem; background: var(--color-surface); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: 4px; }

  .journey-insight { margin-top: 2rem; padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; background: var(--color-surface); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: 10px; font-size: 0.92rem; line-height: 1.65; color: var(--color-text-secondary); text-align: center; }
  .journey-insight strong { color: var(--color-text); }

  /* Test-First */
  .testfirst-section { padding: 4rem 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border); }

  .compare { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr auto 1fr; gap: 1.5rem; align-items: stretch; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .compare-col { background: var(--color-surface); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: 14px; overflow: hidden; }
  .compare-header { padding: 0.75rem 1.25rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 600; text-align: center; }
  .compare-old .compare-header { color: var(--color-text-muted); }
  .compare-new .compare-header { color: var(--color-accent); }
  .compare-body { padding: 1.5rem; display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem; }
  .compare-step { font-size: 0.88rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary); text-align: center; padding: 0.5rem 1rem; background: var(--color-surface-raised); border-radius: 6px; width: 100%; }
  .compare-step.highlight { background: rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.1); color: var(--color-accent); font-weight: 600; border: 1px solid rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.2); }
  .compare-step.dim { opacity: 0.5; }
  .compare-arrow { color: var(--color-text-muted); opacity: 0.4; font-size: 0.8rem; }
  .compare-vs { display: flex; align-items: center; font-size: 0.8rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--color-text-muted); text-transform: uppercase; }

  .why-box { padding: 1.5rem 2rem; background: var(--color-surface); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent); border-radius: 10px; }
  .why-box h3 { font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .why-box p { color: var(--color-text-muted); font-size: 0.92rem; line-height: 1.65; }
  .why-box strong { color: var(--color-text-secondary); }

  /* Verify */
  .verify-section { padding: 4rem 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border); }

  .verify-pipeline { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }
  .verify-step { display: flex; gap: 1rem; align-items: flex-start; padding: 1.25rem; background: var(--color-surface); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: 10px; }
  .v-num { flex-shrink: 0; width: 32px; height: 32px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; background: var(--color-primary-glow); color: var(--color-primary); border-radius: 8px; font-weight: 800; font-size: 0.8rem; font-family: var(--font-mono); }
  .v-body h4 { font-size: 0.95rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 0.25rem; }
  .v-body p { color: var(--color-text-muted); font-size: 0.88rem; }
  .v-body code { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.82rem; background: var(--color-surface-raised); padding: 0.1rem 0.35rem; border-radius: 4px; }

  .verify-result { background: var(--color-surface); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: 14px; overflow: hidden; }
  .result-header { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.75rem; padding: 1rem 1.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); font-size: 0.9rem; font-weight: 600; }
  .result-badge { font-size: 0.7rem; font-weight: 700; padding: 0.2rem 0.5rem; border-radius: 4px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.04em; }
  .result-pass { background: rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.15); color: #10b981; }
  .result-body { padding: 1rem 1.5rem; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.625rem; }
  .result-row { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; font-size: 0.88rem; }
  .result-row span:first-child { color: var(--color-text-muted); }
  .result-value { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-accent); }
  .result-footer { padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border); font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--color-text-muted); font-style: italic; }

  /* CTA */
  .cta-section { padding: 4rem 0 6rem; text-align: center; border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .cta-section h2 { font-size: 1.75rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .cta-section p { color: var(--color-text-muted); margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .cta-actions { display: flex; gap: 0.75rem; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .btn { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem; padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem; border-radius: 10px; font-size: 0.9rem; font-weight: 600; font-family: var(--font-sans); transition: all 0.2s; border: none; cursor: pointer; }
  .btn-primary { background: var(--color-primary); color: white; }
  .btn-primary:hover { background: var(--color-primary-hover); color: white; transform: translateY(-1px); }
  .btn-ghost { background: var(--color-surface); color: var(--color-text); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .btn-ghost:hover { border-color: var(--color-border-hover); color: var(--color-text); transform: translateY(-1px); }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .page-hero { padding: 3rem 1.5rem 2rem; }
    .compare { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .compare-vs { justify-content: center; padding: 0.25rem 0; }
    .artifact { flex-direction: column; gap: 0.25rem; }
    .a-label { min-width: auto; }
  }
</style>
